==English==

===Adjective===
'''down to a science'''

Perfected.  The sentence ''I have my painting technique down to a science.'' means ''I have my painting technique perfected.''.  Practiced ease and confidance.

====Usage Notes====
Usually used after ''have <something>''.  Having something down to a science implies skill built through long practice or repitition.  E.g. ''Painting the first few rooms was difficult; the next were easier, but now I have it down to a science.''.